article_title: Kentucky counties with highest Medicaid rates backed Matt Bevin, who plans to cut Medicaid
article_text: The 66 percent of Owsley County that gets health coverage through Medicaid now must reconcile itself with the 70 percent that voted for Republican Governor-elect Matt Bevin, who pledged to cut the state's Medicaid program and close the state-run Kynect health insurance exchange.
